						               													<description>Based on the hit boardgame and the award-winning roleplaying game! &amp;#10;&amp;#10;CONSIDER WHAT I HAVE TOLD YOU, BARBARIAN,&amp;rdquo; SAID XALTOTUN. &amp;ldquo;YOU WILL HAVE PLENTY OF LEISURE. I HAVE NOT YET DECIDED WHAT I SHALL DO WITH YOU. IT DEPENDS ON CIRCUMSTANCES YET UNBORN. BUT LET THIS BE IMPRESSED UPON YOU: THAT IF I DECIDE TO USE YOU IN MY GAME, IT WILL BE BETTER TO SUBMIT WITHOUT RESISTANCE THAN TO SUFFER MY WRATH.&amp;rdquo; &amp;#10;&amp;#10;Since the introduction of fantasy into wargaming, Robert E. Howard&amp;rsquo;s Conan has loomed large across popular culture, recently inspiring the award-winning Robert E. Howard&amp;rsquo;s Conan: Adventures in an Age Undreamed Of roleplaying game and Monolith&amp;rsquo;s hit Conan boardgame. Here, for the first time ever, is the crossover between these two games: miniatures and roleplaying adventure meet in the Hyborian Age!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Developed closely with Monolith Entertainment, The Monolith Sourcebook provides players and gamemasters with a host of exciting material: new campaigns for both games, standalone adventures, and advice for creating original boardgame adventures using the roleplaying resources. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A Red Tide to Kush, a complete boardgame campaign with ten new scenarios. &amp;#10;    A solo/cooperative campaign made up of nine new scenarios for the boardgame. &amp;#10;    Shadows from Gulsaggah, a complete roleplaying adventure campaign set in the legendary Black Coast. &amp;#10;    Rules for solo and cooperative play for the boardgame. &amp;#10;    Guidelines for using Conan tiles and roleplaying resources to create new scenarios for the boardgame.&amp;#10;    Characters, monsters, equipment, and artifacts, from Amboola the Spearman to Xuthal&amp;rsquo;s Crown&amp;#10;    Get the most out of Monolith&amp;rsquo;s Conan boardgame with this essential sourcebook!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Requires two Conan tile sets &amp;mdash; Perilous Ruins &amp;amp; Forgotten Cities and Forbidden Places &amp;amp; Pits of Horror &amp;mdash; to play; the Conan (English King Pledge Edition) for tabletop action; and the Robert E. Howard&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#153;s Conan: Adventures in an Age Undreamed Of core rulebook for roleplaying game excitement.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
